Differences between modelName, modelFileName, filename, directory and how I will try to handle them.


In TauP_Create, these two are currently just set as default, but should eventually be user-supplied:

self.directory = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(
            inspect.getfile(inspect.currentframe()))), "data")
--> gives './data'. Used as input (v model) AND output directory (tau model)

self.modelFilename = "iasp91.tvel"
--> used directly e.g. in this call to read an 'internally stored file':
    self.vMod = TauModelLoader.loadVelocityModel(self.modelFilename)

filename = os.path.join(self.directory, self.modelFilename)
--> whole (relative or absolute, dependds) path, e.g. ./data/iasp91.tvel

modelName = os.path.basename(filename)  to strip the directory path
modelName = modelName[:-5]    (in the case of .tvel)
--> e.g. iasp91. Used so far in VelocityModel.

